article.headline: Tennessee Tech 85, Brevard College 41
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Milone Clark hit every shot Monday night, scoring 15 points and leading Tennessee Tech to an 85-41 victory over Brevard. Clark was 7-of-7 from the floor and made his only 3-point shot. Tech (7-2) led all the way after Keyon Boyd hit a 3-pointer to make it 5-3 with 17:43 left in the first half. Brevard (3-12) trailed 40-16 at halftime. Derek Stribling added 12 points for Tennessee Tech and Anthony Fisher scored 11. Fourteen Golden Eagles played and 13 scored. Brevard was led by Brian Davison with 14 points and Rashad Mosley with 11. The Golden Eagles shot 56.6 percent for the game, including 59.3 percent in the second half. Brevard shot just 31.7 percent, including 23.5 percent in the first half.
